for use docker in docker folder find daemon.json file
and add this
{
    "registry-mirrors": ["https://registry.docker.ir"]
}
install redis by docker
after run container from redis image
in cli mode:

redis-cli ping --> pong
redis-cli set keyName value
redis-cli get keyName
redis-cli dbsize -> show count of value
redis-cli keys '*' -> show all key
redis-cli exists key -> show key exist or not
redis-cli keys 'a' -> show all key has a char
redis-cli flushall -> clean all cache
redis-cli config get *memory* -> show memory configuration 
redis-cli info stats -> show state of redis
redis-cli connection info> --bigkeys -> show big key
